cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.CY, cs.IR, cs.MM

This paper deals with predicting popularity of content in social media, which involves analyzing user behavior and interactions on social media sites. This falls under the scope of social computing (cs.SI) and social network analysis (cs.SD). The paper also discusses the influence of web site design on user behavior, which could be categorized under human-computer interaction (cs.CY). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of differential pricing for access to content or ad placement, which could be related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and multimedia (cs.MM).
